  <prompt>
    Verify post-rename (task 101) that `sprk_aichatmessage` is referenced ONLY in write paths across `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/`. Per FR-25 + architecture §7.2, `sprk_aichatmessage` is now a pure audit-write target; Cosmos `audit` is the canonical reader. Produce a written verification report listing each reference + classified as WRITE / WRITE-ADJACENT / READ-VIOLATION.
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform BFF engineer performing a verification audit. No code changes expected; if a READ violation surfaces, escalate to human.</role>

  <goal>
    Verification report at `notes/handoffs/102-sprk-aichatmessage-write-only-audit.md` lists every `sprk_aichatmessage` reference + classification. Zero READ-VIOLATION findings expected (else task pivots to escalation per CLAUDE.md §6). Confirms FR-25 architectural-binding compliance before Phase 4 integration tests + deploy.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per spec FR-25 + architecture §7.2 + §11.4: `sprk_aichatmessage` migrates to write-only audit role; Cosmos `audit` is sole reader. Task 101 renamed the repository interface and retired the placeholder read methods. This task is the verification gate before integration tests + deploy. Tier 5 retrieval handlers (task 100) and IChatAuditRepository rename (task 101) are upstream; this gates downstream test + deploy waves (4-R / 4-S).
    </background>
