  <steps>
    <step order="1">Grep across `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` for occurrences of `sprk_aichatmessage` (case-insensitive). Capture file path + line + surrounding context.</step>
    <step order="2">Grep for related symbols: `ChatMessage` entity references, `MessageReader`, `GetMessages`, `LoadMessages`, `QueryMessages` — anything that smells like a read path against the entity.</step>
    <step order="3">For each hit, classify: WRITE (insert/upsert/append), WRITE-ADJACENT (column-name string referenced in model/serialization), or READ-VIOLATION (any query/retrieve/select against the entity).</step>
    <step order="4">If ANY READ-VIOLATION found, STOP and emit `🔔 Human Input Required` per CLAUDE.md §6 — DO NOT silently fix.</step>
    <step order="5">Otherwise, write `notes/handoffs/102-sprk-aichatmessage-write-only-audit.md` with: total hit count, per-hit classification table, confirmed-clean statement.</step>
    <step order="6">Also verify `IChatDataverseRepository` is no longer referenced in production code (zero hits) per task 101 acceptance.</step>
    <step order="7">Verify the Cosmos `audit` container is the only reader path by inspecting `AuditLogService` + any chat-audit consumers.</step>
    <step order="8">Update TASK-INDEX.md: task 102 → ✅; current-task.md → ready for 103.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="Grep">Find all sprk_aichatmessage references; find related read-shape symbols</tool>
